works.description: The spring auction season has begun, and the Sotheby’s Impressionist and Modern Art sale has brought in $170.5 million for 44 works sold out of 59 on offer. Although the sales figure falls between the pre-sale estimate of $159 million and $230 million, the total is far below last year’s parallel sale that made $196 million. Leading the chart was a 1934 Picasso painting titled “Femmes lisant (deux personnages)” that went for $21.4 million. It was earlier expected to sell for up to $35 million.
